Name: Carbon
Description:
The building block of all organic life. Of critical importance to space travellers, as Carbon is used to recharge mining equipment.
 
The Mining Laser will harvest Carbon from trees, plants, and all other forms of vegetable.

Name: Condensed Carbon
Description:
Advanced material, processed from regular carbon in a Refiner.

The increased molecule density offers a substantially improved energy-per-gram ratio.

Occasionally found in crystalline form. Harvesting large crystals may require a Advanced Mining Laser.

Name: Oxygen
Description:
Integral to the atmospheric filtering technology at the heart of the exosuit life support system.

Exosuit material processing allows oxygen to be harvested directly from appropriate planetary flora.

Other plantlife may be scanned with the Analysis Visor to reveal alternative oxygen supplies.

Name: Hexite
Description: An odourless, mineral-rich substance with a hexagonal crystalline structure, harvested from the faecal matter of a creature.

Name: Di-hydrogen
Description:
A stable, crystalline form of hydrogen remarkable both for its extreme energy density and its stability at atmospheric pressures.

Common to all worlds, Di-hydrogen is found in the form of large blue crystals. It is a key component of Starship Launch Fuel.

Name: Deuterium
Description:
A stable hydrogen isotope used heavily in both small-scale fusion reactors and neutron-scattering shield technology.

Deuterium very rarely occurs naturally. Most of the galaxy's supply comes from the processing of Di-hydrogen in Refiners.

Name: Tritium
Description:
Radioactive isotope commonly used to fuel the fusion reactor at the heart of starship Pulse Engines.

Abundant in interstellar asteroid fields, Tritium can be mined from asteroids using starship weaponry.

Name: Ferrite Dust
Description:
An abundant mineral element, found in rock formations and other areas of geological interest. Easily extracted using a Mining Laser.

Typically requires processing in a Refiner before use in construction or technology manufacture.

Name: Pure Ferrite
Description:
Processed metal, free of dust and pebbles. Used to construct a wide variety of structures and technologies.

Typically purified from Ferrite dust using a Refiner, but can occasionally be found in large deposits. Collection may require an Advanced Mining Laser.

Name: Magnetised Ferrite
Description:
Highly processed metal, requiring several stages of processing in a Refiner.

Used in the creation of advanced structures and technologies. Avoid ingestion.

Name: Silicate Powder
Description:
An abundant mineral element, found within the geological strata of all rocky worlds. Easily extracted using a Terrain Manipulator. Create a tunnel anywhere to begin extraction.

Process in a Refiner to create Glass.

Name: Sodium
Description:
A powerful catalyst, useful for charging defensive technologies such as shields or hazard protection.
 
Exosuit material handling technology allows automatic harvesting from appropriate sodium-rich flora.

A vital ingredient in the creation of many advanced devices, products and components.

Name: Sodium Nitrate
Description:
An advanced catalyst, useful for charging defensive technologies such as shields or hazard protection.
 
Created in a Refiner, or occasionally found in crystalline form on a planet's surface.

Offers a substantially improved energy-per-gram ratio over regular Sodium.

Name: Cobalt
Description:
Mined from underground minerals, cobalt is found in plentiful supply in caves and caverns. Useful in the manufacture of Ion Batteries.

It is used in the creation of several technologies and structures, and can be processed in a Refiner to make the most of its inherent charge.

Name: Ionised Cobalt
Description:
A highly energised form of Cobalt, this processed metal can be used to create Advanced Ion Batteries, a conveniently portable source of energy for the Exosuit.

In widespread use as a key component in the creation of advanced technologies and structures.

Name: Salt
Description:
A naturally occuring salt, found in abundance in underwater minerals.

Can be processed in a Refiner to create Chlorine. This refined form is used in the manufacture of advanced products and technologies.

Name: Chlorine
Description:
A reactive element most easily harvested by processing the salt-infused minerals found in oceans.

Used in the manufacture of advanced technologies.

Name: Cyto-Phosphate
Description:
A blue-green organic compound produced during the metabolic cycle of deep-sea plantlife. Rich in soluble energy, cyto-phosphates are crucial in many submarine technologies.
 
The Mining Laser will harvest cyto-phosphate compounds from underwater flora.

Name: Copper
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star. Such stellar material ends up forming deposits in the crust of local planets.

Copper is found on planets orbiting yellow stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal for use in the manufacture of advanced technologies.

Name: Cadmium
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star. Such stellar material ends up forming deposits in the crust of local planets.

Cadmium is found on planets orbiting red stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal for use in the manufacture of advanced technologies.

Name: Emeril
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star.

Emeril is found on planets orbiting green stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal for use in the manufacture of advanced technologies.

Name: Indium
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star. Such stellar material ends up forming deposits in the crust of local planets.

Indium is found on planets orbiting blue stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal for use in the manufacture of advanced technologies.

Name: Chromatic Metal
Description:
A processed metal alloy, created in a Refiner from the stellar metals: Copper, Cadmium, Emeril and Indium.

The rarer the stellar metal, the more Chromatic Metal it will produce.

This valuable metal is used in the creation of many advanced technologies.

Name: Paraffinium
Description:
Local mineral extract, typically found in large deposits or extracted from common minerals after inspection with an Analysis Visor.

Typically found on planets with a tropical environment.

Name: Pyrite
Description:
Local mineral extract, typically found in large deposits or extracted from common minerals after inspection with an Analysis Visor.

Typically found on planets with a desert environment.

Name: Ammonia
Description:
Local mineral extract, typically found in large deposits or extracted from common minerals after inspection with an Analysis Visor.

Typically found on planets with a toxic environment.

Name: Uranium
Description:
Local mineral extract, typically found in large deposits or extracted from common minerals after inspection with an Analysis Visor.

Typically found on planets with a radioactive environment.

Name: Dioxite
Description:
Local mineral extract, typically found in large deposits or extracted from common minerals after inspection with an Analysis Visor.

Typically found on planets with a frozen environment.

Name: Phosphorus
Description:
Local mineral extract, typically found in large deposits or extracted from common minerals after inspection with an Analysis Visor.

Typically found on planets with a scorched environment.

Name: Mordite
Description:
Despite much study, little is known about this haunting, crystalline compound.

It is released from the cadavers of dying creatures, but can also be specifically cultivated and harvested from the Mordite Root plant.

Name: Pugneum
Description:
This oily, unsettling liquid leaks from the circuitry of Sentinels.

Prized by the Vy'keen, Pugneum is thought to share some essential properties with Nanites. It hums in a sinister fashion upon contact with organic matter.

Name: Silver
Description:
Valuable interstellar trading mineral, typically mined from asteroids. Occasionally found in underground planetary deposits.

Prized by people in all systems for its lustre and shine.

Name: Gold
Description:
Highly valuable interstellar trading mineral, typically mined from asteroids. Occasionally found in underground planetary deposits.

Universally prized for its beauty and versatility.

Name: Platinum
Description:
Extremely valuable interstellar trading mineral, typically mined from asteroids. Occasionally found in underground planetary deposits.

Universally prized for its hardiness and versatility.

Name: Sulphurine
Description:
A pungent atmospheric gas. High concentrations are extremely hazardous to organic life.

With the aid of specialised machinery, can be extracted from the atmospheres of Scorched and Desert planets.

Name: Radon
Description:
A colourless, odourless gas with a relatively short half-life. 

Found in both Radioactive and Frozen atmospheres, this gas is produced by the decay of other high-energy elements.

Name: Nitrogen
Description:
A reactive atmospheric gas found wherever there is organic life.

Nitrogen is readily harvested from the atmospheres of Lush and Toxic planets.

Name: Activated Copper
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star.

This Copper has been activated by the extreme conditions in which it was formed, and is highly valuable.

Copper is found on planets orbiting yellow stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal.

Name: Activated Cadmium
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star.

This Cadmium has been activated by the extreme conditions in which it was formed, and is highly valuable.

Cadmium is found on planets orbiting red stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal.

Name: Activated Emeril
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star.

This Emeril has been activated by the extreme conditions in which it was formed, and is highly valuable.

Emeril is found on planets orbiting green stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal.

Name: Activated Indium
Description:
A chromatic metal, generated by fusion in the heart of a star.

Indium is found on planets orbiting blue stars, and can be placed in a Refiner to create purified Chromatic Metal.

This Indium has been activated by the extreme conditions in which it was formed, and is highly valuable.

Name: Fungal Mould
Description:
An oddly-glowing substance, harvested from the gills of Fungal Clusters.

The host plant requires a toxic climate to thrive in the wild, but can be farmed in all environments with the aid of a Hydroponics Tray.

Name: Frost Crystal
Description:
A beautiful blue crystal, this organic compound possesses both great hardiness and a shimmering translucence. It is harvested from the leaves of Frostwort.

Frostwort requires frozen conditions to thrive in the wild, but can be farmed in all environments with the aid of a Hydroponics Tray.

Name: Gamma Root
Description:
A strange substance that seems to slowly shift the air around it. It is found in the roots of the Gamma Weed plant.

Gamma Weed requires high background radiation to thrive in the wild, but can be farmed in all environments with the aid of a Hydroponics Tray.

Name: Cactus Flesh
Description:
Succulent, edible cactus flesh from the Echinocactus plant. As well as being juicy on the tongue, the flesh has many industrial uses.

The Echinocactus thrives only on desert planets, but can be farmed in all environments with the aid of a Hydroponics Tray..

Name: Solanium
Description:
A powerful chemical that has resisted attempts at synthesis. It can be harvested from the bark of the Solar Vine.

The vine requires a hot climate to thrive in the wild, but can be farmed in all environments with the aid of a Hydroponics Tray.

Name: Star Bulb
Description:
A beautiful gemstone, this prized product is the engorged, luminescent berry of the Star Bramble.

The host plant requires lush conditions to thrive in the wild, but can be farmed in all environments with the aid of a Hydroponics Tray.

Name: Marrow Bulb
Description:
A glowing organic bulb, harvested from the Cave Marrow plant found growing underground.

The Cave Marrow has proved resistant to domestication, and no farmable cultivars are known to exist. As such, marrow bulbs must be harvested by hand in the wild.

Name: Kelp Sac
Description:
A rubbery, luminescent sac harvested from underwater Candle Kelp plants.

Agricultural science has not yet tamed the Candle Kelp. As such, these sacs cannot be farmed.

Name: Faecium
Description:
A foul-smelling compound that can be harvested from the Gutrot Flower, or less desirably from the faecal matter of some species.

Creatures can be fed to encourage the formation and deposition of faecium crystals.

Name: Residual Goop
Description:
A pulsating, foul smelling goop that builds up in poorly-maintained machinery.

Skin contact is not advised.

Name: Runaway Mould
Description:
An out of control mould growth that builds up in poorly-maintained machinery.

Likely to be several different species of mould, merged together into one super-colony.

Name: Rusted Metal
Description:
Handfuls of corroded metal, distorted by years of exposure to the harsh environment.

Handle with care.

Name: Living Slime
Description:
A heavy, oozing slime. It is moving gently, as if it has a heartbeat of its own.

Nutrient source: unknown.

Name: Viscous Fluids
Description:
An unnaturally thick liquid of dubious colour. Its origins are impossible to fathom.

Appears to have some mild magnetic properties.

Name: Nanite Cluster
Description:
A dense miasma of Nanites, undulating in its potentiality. These clusters are stable, but unrestricted nanite foam can produce undesirable runaway reactions in the presence of organic matter.

Used in the construction of advanced technologies. Highly valuable to specialist traders.

Name: QUICKSILVER
Description: Currency or faction standing, given as a reward.

Name: UNITS
Description: Currency or faction standing, given as a reward.

Name: Antimatter
Description:
Contained negative matter and baryogenesis antiparticles.
 
The vast energy potential of antimatter makes it highly valuable. 95% of existing antimatter consumption is in the powering of starship hyperdrives.

WARNING: uncontained usage is not recommended.

Name: Antimatter Housing
Description:
Secure antimatter containment device, required before Antimatter can be safely secured as Warp Cells.

Rebound Oxygen forms a protective gas pocket, preventing the antimatter from reacting with the surrounding casing.

Name: Carbon Nanotubes
Description:
Metres and metres of high capacity carbon nanotubes.

Their high tensile strength and mild conductivity make these a key component in many advanced technologies.

Name: Cobalt Mirror
Description:
A specialist optical component.

Employing a polished cobalt surface, this mirror is able to selectively filter different wavelengths of light, changing its reflective pattern based on nearby magnetic fields.

Name: Hermetic Seal
Description:
A high-performance carbon seal, able to withstand both the harsh interstellar environment and the rigours of intensive, high-energy industrial use.

User is advised to regularly check seal integrity after installation.

Name: Metal Plating
Description:
A lightweight metal product, heavily used in the manufacture of starship parts and deployable technology. A mainstay of the construction industries of all known primary species.

Crafted from Ferrite Dust.

Name: Microprocessor
Description:
A compact, low-heat microchip. Assembled from processed Chromatic Metal, created from one of several specialised terrain metals.

Used in the creation of a wide range of advanced technologies.

Name: Oxygen Filter
Description:
A specialist technology component.

This small device can rapidly change the gaseous environment within a device, handling conditions from total vacuum to pure oxygen atmospheres.

Name: Salt Refractor
Description:
A specialist technology component, vital to the complex internals of modern laser systems. 

This light-scattering device takes advantage of the unique optical properties of stabilised and polished salt, to both slow and refract passing photons.

Name: Sodium Diode
Description:
An advanced circuit component.

The refined sodium electrode within its vacuum tube gives this diode specialist surge-protection capabilities.

Name: Di-hydrogen Jelly
Description:
A faintly-glowing jelly. Its gentle light and soft wobble belie the fact that this sticky gel is both highly toxic and highly flammable. Skin contact is to be avoided at all costs.

Synthesised from Di-hydrogen.

Name: Fuel Oxidiser
Description:
A temporary frigate upgrade that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful fuel upgrade overloads frigate engines, allowing for faster-than-usual travel.

Name: Explosive Drones
Description:
A temporary frigate upgrade that lasts for one expedition.

This pack of autonomous explosives have been programmed to launch from the fleet and pilot themselves directly towards hostile vessels. Extremely dangerous.

Name: Holographic Analyser
Description:
A temporary frigate upgrade that lasts for one expedition.

This powerful analytic computer overclocks the existing fleet systems, allowing for faster-than-light calculations. Heat is a problem, and the chips do not last long.

Name: Mind Control Device
Description:
A temporary frigate upgrade that lasts for one expedition.

The mind control device plugs into the ship's trading and communications systems, allowing the Fleet Commander to gain the upper hand in any negotiation.

Name: Mineral Compressor
Description:
A temporary frigate upgrade that lasts for one expedition.

The mineral compressor allows fleet mining crews to liquidise the substances they extract, for both faster processing and easier transportation.

Name: Warp Cell
Description:
This antimatter-based fuel is one of the few power sources capable of meeting the incredible energy requirements of a starship hyperdrive.

Secured within a robust housing, the cell is guarenteed paradox-free during FTL travel.

Name: Warp Hypercore
Description:
A high-capacity antimatter-based fuel, this cell harnesses an internal black hole generator to power starship hyperdrives across multiple warp jumps.

Cell walls are specially designed to reflect any reality paradoxes back towards the heart of the unit, where they generate additional power.

Name: Unstable Plasma
Description:
Densely-packed fuel capsule for use in the Plasma Launcher.
 
Contained highly-pressurised electro-thermal energy for use in land disruption grenade technology.

Name: Ion Battery
Description:
Convenient and optimised power storage unit. Used in a wide variety of defensive and hazard protection systems.
 
Constructed by fusing Ferrite Dust with underground Cobalt. Frequently found ready-made in cylindrical metal containers.

Name: Advanced Ion Battery
Description:
Powerful energy storage unit. Used in a wide variety of defensive and hazard protection systems.

Constructed from Ionised Cobalt and Pure Ferrite, and occasionally found in cylindrical metal containers.

Name: Starshield Battery
Description:
A power storage unit optimised for use in starship defensive systems.
 
Tritium-fuelled capacitors provide quick-release charge for the Deflector Shield, but would overload smaller-scale equipment.

Name: Life Support Gel
Description:
Emergency life support fuel.

Synthesised from rocket fuel crystals and carbon, this gel offers a temporary boost to life support systems. Long-term impact on user's lungs is currently unknown.

Name: Oxygen Capsule
Description:
Stablised and secure life support filtration gas.

Easily assembled from Oxygen and Ferrite Dust. Offers an efficient method for long-term life support power.

Name: Frigate Fuel (50 Tonnes)
Description:
A small barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

Name: Frigate Fuel (100 Tonnes)
Description:
A large barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

Name: Frigate Fuel (200 Tonnes)
Description:
A huge barrel of frigate fuel.

This viscous gel is highly toxic to the touch. A refined fuel, it powers the interstellar engines of large trading ships.

Name: Starship Launch Fuel
Description:
Highly reactive solid-state fuel, required to fuel Starship Launch Thrusters.

Created from crystallised Di-hydrogen, found in blue deposits on all worlds.

Name: Hydrothermal Fuel Cell
Description:
A high thermal energy fuel, contained within a standardised fuel cell. Used to fuel the Humboldt Drive that powers the Nautilon submarine.

Created with a mix of organic compounds (Carbon and cyto-phosphates) and localised mineral salts.

Name: Projectile Ammunition
Description:
Advanced munition fragments, constructed to fit Universal Multi-Tool Standard 07/FF1.

Easily inserted into the Boltcaster, Pulse Spitter and Scatter Blaster via the Multi-Tool clip reloading system.

Name: Carbon Crystal
Description:
Hyper-compressed carbon, this substance's dense nanostructure makes it highly valuable as both an energy source and a technology component.

Synthesised from Condensed Carbon.

Name: Chloride Lattice
Description:
A tightly-bonded form of Chlorine. Rigidly-packed molecules offer unrivalled conductivity. Not known to form spontaneously: creation requires highly-focused energy inputs.

Synthesised from Chlorine.

Name: Destablised Sodium
Description:
Sodium is typically highly stable, but certain configurations retain the reactivity of its component ions. User is advised to wear Hazardous Material Gauntlets before handling.

Synthesised from Sodium.

Name: Rare Metal Element
Description:
A highly-prized metal product, this rare element is used in the manufacture of several advanced technologies.

Metal is highly reactive and quickly bonds to exposed skin. User is advised to handle with extreme caution.

Synthesised from Magnetised Ferrite.

Name: Superoxide Crystal
Description:
A para-magnetic form of Oxygen, this rare substance has much to offer in the production of advanced technologies. Requires conversion prior to input into Life Support systems. Direct inhalation is NOT recommended.

Synthesised from Oxygen.

Name: TetraCobalt
Description:
A novel molecular form of Cobalt, requiring very high energy levels to create. Natural occurrence is extremely rare.

Synthesised from Ionised Cobalt.

Name: Acid
Description:
Dilute acid for high current generation in diverse power cells.

Crafted from Mordite and Fungal Mould.

Name: Heat Capacitor
Description:
A thermal regulator produced from refined organic material. It is unique it its ability to produce, dissipate and distribute heat as required.

Crafted from Solanium and Frost Crystals.

Name: Poly Fibre
Description:
A connective fibre for electronics, made from an advanced synthetic polymer and capable of serving as a conduit for power and data.

Crafted from Cactus Flesh and Star Bulbs.

Name: Circuit Board
Description:
Stackable, semi-flexible circuit board made from a highly durable synthetic polymer.

Crafted from Heat Capacitors and Poly Fibre.

Name: Glass
Description:
Shatter-proof, scratch-resistant glass with a self-cleaning, UV-cured coating, for general construction use.

Refined from Silicate powder. Extract silicate from the earth with a Terrain Manipulator.

Can be crafted from Frost Crystals extracted from plants on frozen worlds.

Name: Unstable Gel
Description:
A highly reactive gel, this substance is both energy-rich and dangerous to touch.

Crafted from Cactus Flesh.

Name: Liquid Explosive
Description:
A general purpose high explosive, offered in liquid form for convenience of transport and deployment. Do not drink.

Crafted from Acid and Unstable Gel.

Name: Lubricant
Description:
A synthetic lubricant that reduces wear and prolongs the lifespan of technologies with moving parts.

Crafted from Faecium and Gamma Root.

Name: Living Glass
Description:
An advanced building material, this glass has been imbued with organic compounds that allow it to react to the environment. Microbes within the glass filter harmful light of all wavelengths and balance the atmosphere as required.

Crafted from Lubricant and Glass.

Name: Enriched Carbon
Description:
A refined product, taking ordinary carbon and boosting it with radioactive energy.

Crafted from Radon and Condensed Carbon.

Name: Nitrogen Salt
Description:
A refined product, this is a powerful organic fertiliser in an easily distributed form.

Crafted from Nitrogen and Condensed Carbon.

Name: Thermic Condensate
Description:
A refined product, holding the energy potential of heated atmospheric gas in a stable state until required.

Crafted from Sulphurine and Condensed Carbon.

Name: Hot Ice
Description:
A paradoxical material, made less mysterious by its relative ease of manufacture.

Crafted from Enriched Carbon and Nitrogen Salt.

Name: Cryo-Pump
Description:
An advanced, self-regulating hybrid material, the Cryo-Pump distributes heat across itself with near perfect efficiency, making it vital in the creation of thermal regulators.

Crafted from Hot Ice and Thermic Condensate

Name: Semiconductor
Description:
An advanced material useful in many electronic devices, with its own in-built temperature regulator.

Crafted from Thermic Condensate and Nitrogen Salt.

Name: Organic Catalyst
Description:
A catalytic material used in the creation of many organic fertilisers.

Crafted from Thermic Condensate and Enriched Carbon.

Name: Superconductor
Description:
An advanced conductive material, the superconductor further enriches the field-warping power of the Semiconductor.

Crafted from Enriched Carbon and Semiconductors.

Name: Fusion Accelerant
Description:
An advanced fuel source, made from a perfect blend of high potential energy organic materials.

Crafted from Organic Catalyst and Nitrogen Salt.

Name: Cryogenic Chamber
Description:
A low temperature chamber, designed to prevent the natural decay of organic matter.

Crafted from Living Glass and a Cryo-Pump.

Name: Portable Reactor
Description:
A miniature self-controlled nuclear reactor. Generates sub-stellar levels of energy in a hassle-free, widely compatible fuel module.

Crafted from Liquid Explosives and Fusion Accelerant.

Name: Quantum Processor
Description:
A highly advanced computational device, essential for the complex calculations involved in warp travel.

Crafted from Circuit Boards and Superconductors.

Name: Aronium
Description:
A lightweight and highly malleable alloy. Crafted from Paraffinium and Chlorine.

In high demand on the Galactic Trade Network due to its utility in the construction of planetside outposts and facilities.

Name: Dirty Bronze
Description:
A popular metal alloy with a wide variety of uses. 'Dirty Bronze' has shed its scientific name in favour of the popular term for its colour.

Crafted from Pure Ferrite and Pyrite.

Name: Grantine
Description:
Soft workable alloy favoured by artisans throughout the known galaxy. Crafted from Ionised Cobalt and Dioxite.

A popular trading good, with many galactic shipping paths devoted to its sale and transport.

Name: Herox
Description:
Combined neutral alloy with uses that range from pharmacology all the way to heavy industry. Crafted from Chlorine and Ammonia.

Forms the backbone of galactic alloy trading.

Name: Magno-Gold
Description:
Highly prized and lustrous alloy. Popular with traders of all known primary galactic races. Crafted from Ionised Cobalt and Phosphorus.

Easily recognisable by its bright red glow and strong magnetic field.

Name: Lemmium
Description:
Pure Ferrite alloy. Crafted from Pure Ferrite and Uranium.

Used extensively in starship freighter construction due to its sheer strength. A hardcore material popular on the Galactic Trade Network.

Name: Geodesite
Description:
Advanced and durable alloy primarily used in starship hull construction and deep-space exploration drone technology.

Crafted from Herox, Dirty Bronze and Lemmium.

Name: Iridesite
Description:
Advanced light metal alloy traded throughout the galactic Outer Edge. Often used in the interiors of trading shuttles to reduce weight as they ascend from planets with high gravitational fields.

Crafted from Aronium, Magno-Gold and Grantine.

Name: Fusion Ignitor
Description:
A highly advanced piece of technology for use in the next generation of power plants. Producing a fusion core requires both intricate scientific skills and complex industrial processes.

Crafted from Portable Reactor, Quantum Processors and Geodesite.

Name: Stasis Device
Description:
A device specifically crafted to keep lifeforms alive for thousands of years longer than their natural lifespan. Such a device requires great skill to manufacture, as not only is it technically complex, but the consequences for a user in the event of malfunction would be disastrous.

Crafted from Quantum Processors, Cryogenic Chambers, and Iridesite.

Name: Wiring Loom
Description:
A prefabricated circuit board, designed for flexible use in a large range of technology components.

The module features an integrated nanite processor, allowing it to be quickly configured for a wide variety of uses.

Name: Planetary Chart
Description:
A map of a nearby planet. The coordinates of a distress signal have been marked.

Select the map and use Plot Route (FE_ALT1) to pin the location in your Exosuit display.

New maps can be gained by exchanging Navigation Data with a Space Station Cartographer.

Name: Ancient Key
Description: A key of some weight, this aged piece of wrought iron must belong in a nearby lock...

Name: Trident Key
Description:
A strange forked key, glowing with an ultraviolet light.

Despite its primitive appearance, Exosuit scanning systems reveal traces of nanite foam upon its teeth.

Name: Navigation Data
Description:
Encoded navigation data. This highly portable data unit contains all relevant cartographical information for a planetary region.

May be traded with a Cartographer aboard a Space Station in exchange for usable star charts.

Name: Drop Pod Coordinate Data
Description:
Encoded navigation data for input into a Signal Booster.

When properly decrypted, will reveal the location of a Drop Pod containing Exosuit Upgrades.

Name: Log Encryption Key
Description:
A fragment of the encryption override sequence for a freighter's emergency log.

Several parts of the sequence may be required to gain full access to recorded data.

Name: Defence Chit
Description: A token, entitling the bearer to support from the system authorities in dealing with pirate attacks.

Name: Mind Blown
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu to share moments of existential wonder and delight with other explorers.

Name: Celebrate!
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu to share moments of celebration with other explorers.

Name: Ha!
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu to share moments of amusement with other explorers.

Name: Wonder
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu. Gaze up to large structures, fauna, flora, or the stars themselves, and marvel at the insignificance of one small life in all the universe.

Name: No Problem
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu while underwater to signal 'no problem' to other aquatic explorers.

Name: Distant Gaze
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu. Look to the horizon and search for your next adventure.

Name: Heroic Pose
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu. Strike a dramatic pose in front of abandoned structures, towering mineral formations, and colossal predatory lifeforms.

Name: Disbelief
Description:
An exclusive gesture.
This can be selected from the Quick Menu. Fall to your knees in disbelief at the wonders you have seen.

Name: Sparse Horizon Helmet
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.
Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Blazing Orbit Helmet
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.
Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Eye of the Korvax Helmet
Description:
An exclusive Exosuit Appearance Override.
Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: First Spawn Battle Mask
Description:
An aggressive Exosuit Appearance Override, modeled on the war helmets of the ancient Gek.
Transform the appearance of your Exosuit at an Appearance Modifier.

Name: Armoured Shoulderpads
Description: Powerful shoulder armour, this Exosuit augmentation comes with high-voltage connections into the user's skeletal system. This current jolts the user's body as required, manipulating the muscles into their optimal defensive posture.

Name: Armoured Chestpiece
Description: Reinforced yet stylish, this Exosuit chest armour provides excellent abdominal protection without compromising on looks.

Name: Armoured ExoGloves
Description: Armoured gloves, perfect for wielding weapons, impressing martial cultures, and picking really spiky plants.

Name: Armoured Leggings
Description:
Carefully woven nano-fibres make these leggings both flexible and resistant to small-arms fire.

Washing requires specialist equipment.

Name: Armoured Boots
Description:
Reinforced foot protection system with integrated tread-balancing gyroscopes.

Hundreds of years of high-tech research, as applied to footwear.

Name: Quad Servo
Description: A highly sprung motor arm salvaged from inside of a Sentinel patrol unit. It occasionally twitches, as if experiencing the echo of combat.

Name: Walker Brain
Description:
Shifting nanite clusters sewn together with a pugneum filament, this circuit is painfully hot to the touch.

A sinister purple light leaks from deep within its wiring, changing in intensity as it watches its holder.

Name: Mind Arc
Description: A strange piece of technology, a gift from beyond the stars. It shimmers in a way that suggests it is not fully in this world.

Name: Captured Nanode
Description: Atlas Seed containing zonally-shifted quasi-stellar substrate. Warning: do not allow matrix to commune with this dimensional space.

Name: Englobed Shade
Description: This Atlas Shell holds the remains of a parasitic space-borne lifeform, most likely of extra-dimensional origins.

Name: Noospheric Orb
Description: An Atlas Seed capable of resonating on humanoid telepathic frequencies; may attempt to subsume any subordinate intellect in close proximity.

Name: Dark Matter
Description: An Atlas Seed shell encompassing a void element harvested from the collapse state of the last universe. Toxic if ingested.

Name: Dawn's End
Description: Sculpted tau neutrino-boson matrix fixed within an irreplaceable Atlas Seed shell. May be semi-sentient.

Name: Photic Jade
Description: This irreplaceable Atlas Seed is a form of matter-adapted photons coalesced into physical solidity by unknown means.

Name: State Phasure
Description: For unknown reasons, this unique Atlas Seed has been phased out of alignment with this quantum reality. Contents cannot be determined.

Name: Novae Reclaiment
Description: Atlas Seed contains neutronium elements from a catastrophic supernova event that obliterated a sentient civilization in an earlier era.

Name: Modified Quanta
Description: This one-of-a-kind Atlas Seed holds an aesthetically pleasing mathematical construct salvaged from the simulation of an alternate reality.

Name: Heart of the Sun
Description: An Atlas Seed containing a time-locked quantum cilia suspended in a photonic shell. No others are known to exist.

Name: NipNip Buds
Description: A pungent bud harvested from the NipNip plant, often used to produce Gek Nip.

Name: Larval Core
Description: A pulsating jellied orb, this gooey sphere is warm to the touch. Its stench triggers a primal fear in mortal beings, a deep-seated gnawing that begs you to drop it and flee.

Name: Salvaged Data
Description:
The salvageable heart of some ancient technology. Unreadable in its current form.

These databanks can be spent at a Construction Research Unit and used to research new Construction Blueprints.

Name: Living Pearl
Description:
Born in the hearts of enormous glowing molluscs found deep underwater.

Unlike most pearls, this sample is no unliving calcite. Some trace of the mother-clam's consciousness remains within the gem, giving it a lingering, haunting beauty.

Name: Hypnotic Eye
Description:
The eye is cold, almost frozen, to the touch. Nonetheless, it is impossible to escape the feeling it is somehow still alive.

Extended exposure is not recommended. Do not stare back into the eye. Do not stare back. Do not stare back.

Name: Hadal Core
Description:
A highly-pressurised fleshy orb.

One can feel it push back when touched, a flash of bioluminescence stirring in the inky black core of this mysterious object.

Name: Soul Engine
Description:
A powerful organic computing unit.

A glitching beat drives this miracle circuit, performing cycle after cycle in an endless, furious loop of calculation.

Name: Storm Crystal
Description: A rare and highly valuable cluster of storm crystals. These crystalline structures thrive in stormy conditions, and naturally attract lightning strikes, becoming spectacularly luminescent when ionised. Exclusively found on extreme weather planets.

Name: Albumen Pearl
Description:
Gemstone formed over the course of centuries within the egg of a super-incubatory species.

Extremely rare.

Name: Gravitino Ball
Description:
Supersymmetric particle cluster.

Extremely rare and valuable. A product of divergent super-gravitational forces.

Name: Sac Venom
Description:
Stabilised poison sample initially produced by aquatic urchin creatures.

A rare and expensive item on the Galactic Trade Network.

Name: Vortex Cube
Description:
Dense metal objects that, long ago, materialised within subterranean networks throughout the Galaxy.

Extremely rare, and of high value.

Name: Atlas Stone
Description:
A spherical gem that seems to pulsate with red light from its centre.
 
An extremely rare item often associated with ancient monolithic sites.

Name: Hex Core
Description: This strange energy orb constantly vibrates, emitting a low-frequency drone. Slight variations in the pattern repeat over and over, almost as if it is attempting to relay a message.

Name: Geode
Description:
An unusually vibrant and potentially valuable lump of rock.

Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY) and crack open with FE_ALT1.

Name: Crystal Fragment
Description:
A crystalline shard with an unusually dense structure. Potentially highly valuable.

Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY) and crack open with FE_ALT1.

Name: Tritium Hypercluster
Description:
A shard of pure crystalised Tritium.

Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY) and crack open with FE_ALT1.

Name: Gold Nugget
Description:
A highly valuable ore chunk, ready to be processed into Gold.

Select in the Inventory (INVENTORY) and crack open with FE_ALT1.

Name: Crystal Sulphide
Description:
Formed in the incredible, high-pressure furnace of planetary cores, these rich mineral deposits have an almost glass-like quality.

Has a wide variety of industrial uses, taking advantage of both its mineral content and its extreme strength under pressure.

Name: Vy'keen Tablet
Description:
A stone tablet bearing line after line of intricate runes. The words are unintelligible, an ancient dialect forgotten by all but the oldest of the Vy'keen elders.

The hand that carved this stone must have been extraordinary. The stonework is precise, delicate - and yet perfectly conveys the unyielding aggression its writer clearly possessed.

Name: Divergence Cube
Description:
A glitching, pulsing data unit. It does not seem to belong in this reality.

The cube gives the impression of a silent scream, the frozen cries of hundreds of lost minds trapped within.

Name: Gek Relic
Description:
A metal statuette of a creature with a coin placed in its beak.
 
Popular with many traders who see it as an emblem of fair commerce and peace.

Name: GekNip
Description:
Edible product much beloved by the Gek.
 
Allows beaked traders to release delightfully scented packets of gas for a prolonged period of time.
 
GekNip gas packets are considered an art form, and the truest representation of the Gek soul.

Name: Vy'keen Effigy
Description:
A small wooden icon carved into the shape of a Sentinel drone.
 
Used by warriors to enter a temporary trance-like state that eliminates their kind's need for sleep.

Name: Vy'keen Dagger
Description: Largely ceremonial weapon. A vital part of Vy'keen tradition and culture.

Name: Korvax Casing
Description:
The metallic shell of a disconnected electronic lifeform that was too distant from its kind to be refreshed with a new entity.
 
Highly prized by all species, not least its own.

Name: Korvax Convergence Cube
Description: Device used by the Korvax for the storage of historical and cultural information.

Name: AtlasPass v1
Description:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.

Provides access to low level restricted areas and outpost systems.

Name: AtlasPass v2
Description:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to mid-tier restricted areas and outpost systems.

Name: AtlasPass v3
Description:
Security and permissions pass granted to specific travellers by many primary galactic species.
 
Provides access to high level restricted areas and outpost systems.

Name: Factory Override Unit
Description:
A portable data unit, compatible with most planetary fabricator facilities.

Once access has been gained to a central control terminal, the Override Unit can divert the facilities resources towards researching new product recipes.

Name: Salvaged Frigate Module
Description:
A technology module harvested from the remains of a large interstellar starship. May be collected from freighter crashsites or salvaged during frigate expeditions.

Useless in its current form, a Research Station aboard your freighter may be able to convert it into useable technology.

Name: Hazard Protection
Description:
The Exosuit's Hazard Protection system continually monitors and stabilises the user's environment. 

General reactive protection may be augmented with Environmental Shields, offering increased protection against specific conditions.

The device is charged with sodium-based substances. User is advised that a failure to charge the Hazard Protection system may allow their environment to become incompatible with life.

Name: Shield Lattice
Description: Increases the base capacity of the Hazard Protection system, allowing the user to spend longer in hazardous environments without recharging their Exosuit.

Name: Life Support
Description:
The core of the Exosuit, the Life Support System continually filters and pumps breathable Oxygen.

In addition to its role in the continued existence of the Exosuit user, the Life Support Unit uses surplus oxygen to generate power for secondary systems, such as the Jetpack, Speed Augmentation and Torch.

Name: Oxygen Recycler
Description: Increases the base capacity of the Life Support system, allowing the user to go longer between charges.

Name: Jetpack
Description:
Provides the Exosuit with advanced movement capabilities, including temporary flight.

Control thrust with JUMP. The flightpack uses energy from the Exosuit Life Support system to pressurise and vent bursts of gas, propelling the user into the air.

Jetpack can be temporarily overloaded by gathering Deuterium-rich plants, causing a dramatic increase in available thrust.

Name: Neural Stimulator
Description: Increases the capacity of the Exosuit's Jetpack Tanks and Adrenal Pump Reserves, allowing the user to both fly and sprint longer.

Name: Rocket Boots
Description:
Equips the Exosuit jetpack with advanced jump capabilities, allowing the user to take huge leaps with ease.

Activate jump systems by rapidly pressing JUMP.

Name: Coolant Network
Description:
User is guarded from extreme heat damage on scorched worlds.

Provides relief from intense atmospheric and solar heat through a threaded dermal distribution network of liquid frenium.

Device is charged by mineral extracts found in hot environments. Operates automatically once constructed within user's exosuit inventory.

Name: Thermic Layer
Description:
User is guarded from extreme cold damage on frozen worlds.

Heat capillaries threaded through a user's suit that evenly distributes liquid calidium to maintain a comfortable body temperature.

Device is charged by mineral extracts found in frozen environments. Operates automatically once constructed within user's exosuit inventory.

Name: Toxic Suppressor
Description:
User is protected from toxic damage.

Reactive compounds within the Suppressor remove toxic liquids that fall on the user, thereby reducing peril and choking hazards.

Device is charged by mineral extracts found in toxic environments. Operates automatically once constructed within user's exosuit inventory.

Name: Radiation Deflector
Description:
User is shielded from radiation damage.

Greatly reduces user peril during the exploration of irradiated worlds. Micro-vibrations increase electromagnetic wave reflection, thereby reducing absorption.

Device is charged by mineral extracts found in radioactive environments. Operates automatically once constructed within user's exosuit inventory.

Name: Aeration Membrane
Description:
User is able to swim underwater for extended periods.

Absorbs gases dissolved in water through a membrane contactor that, if user is of a conventionally structured species, is placed over the mouth or facial breathing hole.

Operates automatically once constructed within user's exosuit inventory.

Name: Haz-Mat Gauntlet
Description:
Upgrades the metallic shielding of the Exosuit's gloves.

An advanced blend of reinforced metal and catalytic shielding allows the user to safely handle hazardous substances, as well perform the necessary feats of strength required to harvest certain farmable flora.

Name: Remembrance
Description: Everything you ever knew is within.

Name: Star Seed
Description:
The smallest of sparks, housed within a containment field of unknown origins.

The seed glows with life, desperate to escape and fulfill its potential.

Name: Obsolete Technology
Description:
A piece of technology, corrupted by interference from the Atlas.

Can be recycled for usable components.

Name: Efficient Water Jets
Description:
Improves the fuel efficiency of the jetpack's marine jets, reducing the drain on Exosuit life support systems.

Aqueous compressor units are installed into the jetpack's turbines, bypassing the large energy requirements of underwater ignition.

Name: Oxygen Rerouter
Description:
Upgrades the Aeration Membrane of the Exosuit to harvest oxygen from the Life Support system in the event of a breathing emergency, allowing the user to resurface and seek conventional fuel supplies.

Note: Long-term conversion of life support energy to breathable gas is not recommended, and may result in life no longer being supported.

Name: Simple Translator
Description:
A automatic translation device. It records and parses nearby conversations before running the data through a contextual learning system to determine intended meaning.

Low memory capacity on this entry-level model limits translation capacity.

Name: Superior Translator
Description:
A automatic translation device. It records and parses nearby conversations before running the data through a contextual learning system to determine intended meaning.

Parallel language processors enable a greater proportion of recorded speech to be translated.

Name: Advanced Translator
Description:
A automatic translation device. It records and parses nearby conversations before running the data through a contextual learning system to determine intended meaning.

A large memory array and overclocked language processors allow the real-time translation of significant chunks of speech.

Name: Artemis' Translator
Description:
A automatic translation device. Device must be calibrated by pre-loading with existing translation data. Device must have network connection to Artemis to function.

Without access to host translation service, on-board circuit allows limited real-time translation of a small number of words.

Name: Pulse Engine
Description:
Spaceflight propulsion, boosts and on-demand Pulse Jumps through local system.
 
User is advised that Tritium is required to charge Pulse Engine. Tritium is abundant in near-space asteroid fields.

Hold ROLLLEFT and ROLLRIGHT together to engage Pulse Jump.
Hold BOOST to initiate in-flight speed boost.

Name: Photonix Core
Description: Provides increased manoeuvrability and longer boosts during spaceflight.

Name: Launch Thruster
Description:
Vital launch and landing gear system.
 
User is advised that specialised, Deuterium-derived fuel is required to recharge thruster. Launch procedures require sufficient fuel levels before activation.
 
Hold THRUST to take off from planet.
Hold BOOST to initiate in-flight speed boost.

Name: Efficient Thrusters
Description: Upgrades the starship launch systems, decreasing the fuel cost of takeoff.

Name: Launch System Recharger
Description:
Photovoltaic panels fitted to the starship Launch Thrusters allow for a slow trickle charge while the ship is not in operation.

Harvested light is used to fuse di-hydrogen from the atmosphere and over time will refuel the Launch Thrusters automatically.

Name: Teleport Receiver
Description:
A device that modulates standard starship communication signals to enable the transport of matter as well as data.

Starships fitted with such a device can send and receive products and substances to a user's exosuit over a long distance.

Name: Hyperdrive
Description:
FTL propulsion drive that allows starship to attain warp speed and jump between neighbouring systems.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems through Galactic Map.

Name: Cadmium Drive
Description:
Hyperdrive computational matrix is upgraded, preventing rapid disassembly when attempting to reach rare-class red stellar bodies.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems via the Galactic Map.

Name: Emeril Drive
Description:
Hyperdrive shield matrix is upgraded, preventing temporal anomalies when attempting to reach rare-class green stellar bodies.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems via the Galactic Map.

Name: Indium Drive
Description:
Hyperdrive protection matrix is upgraded, preventing reality glitches when attempting to reach rare-class blue stellar bodies.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems via the Galactic Map.

Name: Deflector Shield
Description:
Energy shield that protects spacecraft from laser fire, in-flight projectiles and accidental space debris interaction.

User is advised that catalytic elements are required to recharge device.

Operates automatically once constructed within user's starship inventory.

Name: Ablative Armour
Description:
Adds a layer of superheated shielding to the starship's defense array, vaporising incoming fire.

Significantly increases starship shield performance.

Name: Rocket Launcher
Description:
Highly destructive weapon that facilitates rapid ship-to-ship destruction.

Press SHIPFIRE to activate.

Name: Large Rocket Tubes
Description: Expands the loading chamber of the starship Rocket Launcher, improving exhaust performance and allowing for significantly faster heat recovery.

Name: Photon Cannon
Description:
Highly destructive weapon that facilitates rapid ship-to-ship destruction.

Press SHIPFIRE to activate.

Name: Economy Scanner
Description: An upgrade to the starship's galactic-scale sensors. This device allows the user to access detailed economic data about a system without having to visit.

Name: Conflict Scanner
Description: An upgrade to the starship's galactic-scale sensors. This device allows the user to access conflict data in the galaxy map, without having to put themselves in harm's way.

Name: Phase Beam
Description:
Spacefaring beam weapon and asteroid mining tool.

User is advised that organic elements are required to recharge device.

Press SHIPFIRE to activate.

Name: Fourier De-Limiter
Description:
Rewires the Phase Beam with nanite-based circuitry, bypassing conventional reality limits on laser power.

Significantly improves heat performance.

Name: Positron Ejector
Description:
Shots are granted a wide cone of destruction.

With reduced range and rate of fire, users are encouraged to engage their targets in close proximity.

Name: Fragment Supercharger
Description:
Overhauls the firing mechanism of the Positron Ejector, resulting in faster, more accurate particles.

Improves range and accuracy.

Name: Infra-Knife Accelerator
Description:
Releases sustained rapid sequences of fire.

User is advised to limit bursts as overheating can occur very rapidly.

Name: Nonlinear Optics
Description:
Replaces the conventional Photon Cannon optics with an experimental glass array, boosting combat performance.

Significantly improves heat sink capacity.

Name: Cyclotron Ballista
Description: Fires a large, concentrated ball of charged particles at forward targets, causing heavy damage. The charge is non-guided and will continue on its trajectory until it impacts with an obstacle.

Name: Dyson Pump
Description:
Replaces the hint sink of the Cyclotron Ballista by encompassing the entire unit with a heat-absorbing megastructure. Heat output is recycled to boost combat efficiency.

Significantly improves heat performance.

Name: Freighter Hyperdrive
Description: FTL propulsion drive that allows starship to attain warp speed and jump between neighbouring systems.

Name: Freighter Warp Reactor Sigma
Description: Hyperdrive is granted more robust deep space exploration capabilities and ability to leap to stars previously out of reach.

Name: Freighter Warp Reactor Tau
Description: Hyperdrive benefits from advanced fusion that brings starship to higher warp speed and intensity. User's craft will become able to leap deeper into space, and into more distant planetary systems.

Name: Freighter Warp Reactor Theta
Description: Uncapped, yet stabilised, fusion systems are threaded into user's hyperdrive. Allows starship to jump ever longer distances in deep space.

Name: Warp Shielding Sigma
Description:
Hyperdrive computational matrix is upgraded, preventing rapid disassembly when attempting to reach rare-class red stellar bodies.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems via the Galactic Map.

Name: Warp Shielding Tau
Description:
Hyperdrive shield matrix is upgraded, preventing temporal anomalies when attempting to reach rare-class green stellar bodies.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems via the Galactic Map.

Name: Warp Shielding Theta
Description:
Hyperdrive protection matrix is upgraded, preventing reality glitches when attempting to reach rare-class blue stellar bodies.

User is advised to access Hyperdrive systems via the Galactic Map.

Name: Hull Fracture
Description:
Starship subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used for storage or technology until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Rusted Circuits
Description:
Starship subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used for storage or technology until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Shattered Bulwark
Description:
Starship subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used for storage or technology until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Radiation Leak
Description:
Starship subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used for storage or technology until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Containment Failure
Description:
Starship subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used for storage or technology until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Damaged Gears
Description:
Starship subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used for storage or technology until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Analysis Visor
Description:
Specialist Discovery and Survey unit.

Augments standard Scanner capabilities by projecting detailed environmental data directly over the user's visor. Allows the identification of distant points of interest.

The Visor will generate valuable data when used to study flora, fauna and minerals.

Hold AIM to operate. Press ZOOM to zoom.

Name: Scanner
Description:
A Personal Surface Radar augmentation for the Multi-Tool. 

The Scanner releases a high-energy pulse that reveals any critical survival resources in the immediate area. Data is transmitted via the Exosuit directly into the user's visual nervous system.
 
Press SCAN to activate a local scan.

Name: Waveform Recycler
Description:
A powerful lateral processor inserted into the Multi-Tool Scanning System allows the device to recharge at a significantly improved rate.

Increases potential scan frequency.

Name: Survey Device
Description:
A self-contained circuitry upgrade for the Analysis Visor, adding real-time terrain analysis to the scanning array.

Toggle between Visor modes with SURVEYFILTERL/SURVEYFILTERR. Use Surveying Mode to detect hidden terrain resources.

Name: Terrain Manipulator
Description:
Advanced terraforming device. This module overloads existing multi-tool systems, allowing the user to reshape regions as they wish.

Charged with metallic elements.

Name: Personal Forcefield
Description:
On activation, this module draws power from Exosuit Life Support systems to overload the Multi-Tool, distorting the electromagnetic field around the user and creating a powerful personal shield.

While this field offers substantial protection against incoming laser fire, the user is advised that the Multi-Tool cannot be used for other functions while powering the shield.

Name: Combat Scope
Description: A recoil-stabilising weapon scope for precise combat.

Name: Mining Beam
Description:
Multi-Tool Mining Beam powered by Carbon-based Elements. Fire the beam with ATTACK.

Installs focusing optics within the Multi-Tool, allowing it to emit a high-energy beam. The beam is calibrated to excite molecules within common organic or geological objects, allowing it to operate as a highly effective mining device.

WARNING: Destruction of flora, fauna or minerals may attract Sentinel attention.

Name: Advanced Mining Laser
Description:
Replaces standard Mining Beam optics with high-grade Living Glass, allowing the beam to be effective against large and/or rare resource deposits.

The lens adapts automatically to minute fluctuations in the beam waveform, minimising scatter and increasing device mining potential.

Name: Optical Drill
Description:
Wafer-thin lens arrays are arranged in a highly calibrated matrix, focusing the Mining Beam on an atomic level.

This extra precision allows for highly efficient mining. Elements are extracted more efficiently, increasing the yield from items harvested with the Multi-Tool.

Name: Boltcaster
Description:
Generalist weapon attachment for the Multi-Tool. Access fire mode by pressing CYCLEWEAPON and fire weapon with ATTACK.

The Boltcaster reconfigures the Multi-Tool to supercharge Metallic Elements, firing them as high-velocity projectiles capable of causing extreme damage.

Name: Barrel Ioniser
Description:
Inserts a powerful field ionisation device into the barrel of the Boltcaster, increasing projectile stability through the air.

Improves device accuracy and allows the user to fire for longer periods without degrading combat performance.

Name: Boltcaster SM
Description:
Boltcaster shots deliver added physical damage upon impact.

Grants additional kinetic energy to the user's ionised plasma distribution systems.

Operates automatically once constructed within user's Multi-Tool inventory.

Name: Plasma Resonator
Description:
A significant upgrade for the Mining Beam.

Upgrades the Mining Laser's primary crystal chamber, boosting core beam energy while decreasing unwanted heat spill.

Name: Plasma Launcher
Description:
High-impact projectile weapon. Launched plasma shells bounce off surfaces until their internal timer triggers a large explosion.
 
Charged with Unstable Plasma. Careless use can result in damage to user.
 
Press ALTATTACK to activate.

Name: Geology Cannon
Description:
Large-bore projectile launcher. Propels plasma shells designed for rapid ground excavation.
 
Charged with Unstable Plasma. Warning: Explosive hole creation may also damage nearby organic matter.
 
Press ALTATTACK to activate.

Name: Blaze Javelin
Description:
Aggressive weapon attachment for the Multi-Tool. Access fire mode by pressing CYCLEWEAPON and fire weapon with ATTACK.

The Blaze Javelin delivers instantaneous damage on targets.

Plasma charge process creates an ionised gas arc to propel projectiles at great speed. User will perceive destructive results simultaneous to the pull of the trigger.

Name: Mass Accelerator
Description:
Extends the firing chamber of the Blaze Javelin, allowing the internal particle accelerators to reach both greater mass and speed.

Significantly improves weapon damage.

Name: Scatter Blaster
Description:
Specialist close combat weapon attachment for the Multi-Tool. Access fire mode by pressing CYCLEWEAPON and fire weapon with ATTACK.

The Scatter Blaster reconfigures the Multi-Tool to heat and shatter Metallic Elements, firing them in a wide cone of destruction. Range is limited, but the shrapnel is highly effective at close range.

Name: Shell Greaser
Description: Advanced self-lubricating components decrease friction within the Scatter Blaster, offering significant improves to reload times.

Name: Pulse Spitter
Description:
Specialist rapid fire weapon attachment for the Multi-Tool. Access fire mode by pressing CYCLEWEAPON and fire weapon with ATTACK.

The Pulse Spitter redirects Multi-Tool optics to ionise inserted Metallic Elements. These projectiles are launched in a rapid-fire spread, bombarding potential targets with a wave of high-energy plasma.

Name: Amplified Cartridges
Description:
Specialist harmonic resonators allow the Pulse Spitter to split inserted ammunition, effective manufacturing more shots from fewer materials.

Increases weapon clip size.

Name: Short Circuit
Description:
Multi-Tool subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Blown Transistor
Description:
Multi-Tool subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Damaged Wiring
Description:
Multi-Tool subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Rusted Power Core
Description:
Multi-Tool subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Corrupt Module
Description:
Multi-Tool subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Loom Damage
Description:
Multi-Tool subsystem critically damaged.

Slot cannot be used until damage is repaired. Use REPAIR to begin repair process.

Name: Fusion Engine
Description:
A compact fusion core common to all Exocraft.

Requires fuel to function.

Name: Drift Suspension
Description:
Overhauls Exocraft handling values through a combination of software tweaks, pressure adjustments and the insertion of microgravity wells into key suspension components.

Specifically tuned to increase the ability of the Exocraft to drift.

Name: Grip Boost Suspension
Description:
Overhauls Exocraft handling values through a combination of software tweaks, pressure adjustments and the insertion of microgravity wells into key suspension components.

Specifically tuned to increase the ability of the Exocraft to turn sharply.

Name: Hi-Slide Suspension
Description:
Overhauls Exocraft handling values through a combination of software tweaks, pressure adjustments and the insertion of microgravity wells into key suspension components.

Specifically tuned to increase the ability of the Exocraft to slide.

Name: Exocraft Signal Booster
Description:
A large and complex field-based subspace radar.

Due to their large power consumption and inherent subatomic instability, they are found only installed on Exocraft.

Press QUICK_MENU to activate the Signal Booster.

Name: Exocraft Signal Booster Upgrade Sigma
Description: Allows for additional building types to be acquired by the Exocraft Signal Booster.

Name: Exocraft Signal Booster Upgrade Tau
Description: Allows for additional building types to be acquired by the Exocraft Signal Booster.

Name: Exocraft Acceleration Module
Description: An efficient plasma injector coupled to the engine that allows short bursts of speed.

Name: Exocraft Mining Laser
Description: A mining laser too cumbersome for handheld operation, they are found only installed on Exocraft.

Name: Exocraft Mining Laser Upgrade Sigma
Description: Increases power of the Exocraft Mining Laser.

Name: Exocraft Mounted Cannon
Description: Due to the energy requirements of this powerful weapon, they can only be fired from an Exocraft mount.

Name: Humboldt Drive
Description:
A thermally-efficient, inversion-proof reactor engine capable of powering the Nautilon even at extreme depths.

Powered by Hydrothermal Fuel Cells.

Name: Nautilon Cannon
Description:
A mounted cannon specifically designed for the Nautilon Submarine.

A high-energy weapon system, it superheats a small body of water before launching it rapidly towards the intended target.

Designed primarily for damage against biological entities and inefficient when deployed as a mining device.

Name: Tethys Beam
Description:
A mounted laser system specifically designed for the Nautilon Submarine.

Fires a concentrated plasma beam towards the intended target, which is then ignited. Such a trigger mechanism allows the use of high-energy optical mining systems in a liquid medium.

Name: High-Power Sonar
Description:
A high-detail sonar device, capable of upgrading the scanner technology aboard a Nautilon-class submarine to Analysis Visor levels.
Press SCAN to activate the High-Power Sonar.

Name: Osmotic Generator
Description:
Installed into the drive system aboard the Nautilon Submarine.

Captures energy by exploiting the saline gradient in deep water environments, allowing a slow recharge of the Humboldt Drive in the event of fuel emergencies.

Name: Locking mechanism
Description: A simple locking device, designed to keep out unauthorised pilferers. Damage has locked it permanently.

Name: Magnetic Lock
Description: An advanced locking device. A polarity incident has caused it to seal shut permanently.

Name: Superconductive Lock
Description: A highly advanced locking device. Damage to the circuits supplying the magnet has caused it to lock permanently.

Name: Input terminal
Description: A terminal designed to allow manual control of the device. Damage prevents it actually receiving any input.

Name: Bio-input sensor
Description: An advanced control unit, designed to allow device/flesh interaction. Damage prevents it functioning correctly. Interfacing while it is in this state is not advised.

Name: Boiler Unit
Description: A small boiler, generating heat to allow the device to function in difficult climates. A malfunction has resulted in a damaging boiler overflow.

Name: Tiny motor
Description: A very small motor, designed to power very small parts. It has corroded, and is full of very small rust.

Name: Cooling system
Description: A pump and heat exchange system designed to keep the device from overheating. It has itself overheated, and is no longer functional.

Name: Output screen
Description: A display terminal designed to communicate the device's status to the user. As the terminal is broken, the user cannot be made aware that the terminal is broken.

Name: Tamper Prevention Device
Description: A unit designed to destroy vital systems in the event that the device is tampered with by an unauthorised party. Unfortunately, it has itself malfunctioned and will continue to damage other systems until repaired.

Name: Security Alarm
Description: A small light/klaxon hybrid, designed to warn of unauthorised access to the device. Damage to the alarm has caused it to overload and short other nearby circuits.

Name: Spring Casing
Description: The casing for a high-compression spring. The casing has ruptured, causing the spring to shoot out and damage the rest of the device.

Name: Thermoregulator
Description: A control unit designed to keep temperatures even across the device. The sensor unit is damaged, causing it to vent or generate heat at inappropriate times.

Name: Fuel Pump
Description: A high-capacity pump, ensuring that fuel reaches every part of the device in all gravitational conditions. The filter is clogged with a strange substance, causing it to lose power.

Name: Servo Arm
Description: A small mechanical joint, used to correct small mechanical errors across the device. A malfunction is causing it to take functional components and push them into the wrong place, creating even more damage.

Name: Solenoid
Description: A relay switch, intended to aid the powering up of the device. The connectors have become corroded, and the solenoid is no longer functioning.

Name: Pressure Chamber
Description: A small pressurised chamber, designed to create the compressed gas necessary for the device to function. Cracks have appeared in the chamber, causing it to leak.

Name: Master Circuit
Description: The control circuit for all the other components in the device. Damage to this circuitry is fatal.

Name: Power Distributor
Description: The central power unit for the device. Damage to the unit means it is currently distributing all the power to one particular circuit, causing a dangerous short.

Name: Load Balancer
Description: A small unit designed to regulate the flow of power across the device. A malfunction is causing it to short, damaging other components.

Name: Network Interface
Description: A universal network interface, allowing the device to connect to a remote control centre. Damage to this interface is causing it to interpret background radiation as network signals, corrupting data in other circuits.

Name: Safety Panel
Description: The safety panel seals off potentially dangerous components in the event of a malfunction. An over sensitive trigger has caused it to activate, preventing the device from operating.

Name: Alternator
Description: The alternator generates and regulates power for the device. A strange corrosion seeps through it, preventing it from working.

Name: Photovoltaic Panel
Description: A small but efficient panel, designed to harvest light and convert it to power. However, the panel is now cracked and dusty, and can no longer be relied on.

Name: Transmission Box
Description: The gearing mechanism for the device. The lubricant that keeps it operational appears to have been replaced with an otherworldly green goo, and the gears are now stuck.

Name: Ancient Lock
Description: A mysterious lock with several keyholes, this relic protects what must surely be a valuable treasure.

Name: Pearl Offering
Description: The chest requires a Living Pearl, harvested from the giant mother-molluscs that grow on the ocean floor.
